JOHANNESBURG Three men accused of attacking two couples and killing the husbands at Rhodes Park in Kensington, Johannesburg were found guilty in the South Gauteng High Court on Tuesday.Three men accused of murdering two men and raping their wives in #RhodesPark in 2015 have been found guilty by South Gauteng High CourtThe trio -- Edmore Ndlovu, Thabo Nkala and Mduduzi Mathibela - were part of a 12-man gang that attacked Zukisa Khela and Sizwe Jeke at the park s lake in October 2015.READ: Judge begins Rhodes Park judgmentThey had pleaded not guilty to charges of murder, robbery with aggravating circumstances, and rape.Khela and Jeke were attacked while walking with their wives. They were made to strip naked, before their hands were tied and they were drowned.Their wives were repeatedly raped. eNCA